"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Pairs of upper and lower millstones were used for grinding grain in the ancient East. Millstones were common features of the daily life of ordinary people.</p>\n<h2>Millstones as a means of earning a living</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut24:6\">DEU 24:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa47:1-Isa47:2\">ISA 47:1–47:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer25:10\">JER 25:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:22\">REV 18:22</a></p>\n<h2>Millstones were heavy and burdensome</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:6\">MAT 18:6</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:42\">MRK 9:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke17:2\">LUK 17:2</a></p>\n<h2>Millstones as potential weapons</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg9:50-Judg9:53\">JDG 9:50–9:53</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:21\">2SA 11:21</a></p>\n<h2>Millstones in figurative use</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:24\">JOB 41:24</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Millstones as symbols of destructive force</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev18:21\">REV 18:21</a></strong></p>",
